Online [edited]
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/malaria-kyr.jpg>

Emergence of malaria in Kyrgyzstan
----------------------------------
Regarding the upsurge of malaria in Kyrgyzstan, I was struck by the
fact that reported disease rates in this country and neighboring
Tajikistan have approached and even exceeded those of India and
Thailand in recent years. See graph at
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/malaria-kyr.jpg>
--
Professor Steve Berger
Institute of Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
[ProMED thanks Steve Berger for proving open access to these data.
The graph clearly shows the changes in malaria prevalence in
Kyrgyzstan, Tajkistan, India, and Thailand over the past 45 years. - Mod.EP]
